			{
				"type": "Comment",
				"start": 0,
				"end": 365,
				"data": " An inline element sibling immediately before a block: when the block expands, tsv dangles the element's closing > onto its own line so the block head starts fresh (</span⏎>{#if…}); when the block stays inline, the > keeps hugging. The dangle injects no whitespace between </span> and {#if}, so it is render-safe. Prettier keeps the block inline either way. "
			},
